nts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on live AI compliance judgment against regulatory requirements, not just transport or routing. Rejected Workflow because the behavior targets one reviewer’s determination, not chained agentic decisions.","test_description":"Execute real compliance checker on contracts with known compliant/non-compliant outcomes per configured profiles; validate decision accuracy and requirement-level rationale coverage.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments (for example extractor says `standard` but risk assessor says `high risk`), the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior text isolates merge logic: given conflicting reviewer outputs for one clause, preserve both with attribution. This can fail within a single merge function/object without external I/O. Rejected Integration because no explicit cross-module/infra condition is required beyond providing inputs to merge.","test_description":"Call merge function with fixture outputs containing same-clause conflicting labels from extractor and risk assessor; assert merged report keeps both assessments and source attribution fields intact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.62,"Integration":0.34,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"End-to-end orchestration (dispatch all three reviewers, collect outputs, merge unified report) succeeds on a real contract without losing any reviewer findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires chained multi-step pipeline across three AI reviewers plus merge, with correctness depending on sequential agentic handoffs and aggregation compl